WEBVTT

00:05.826 --> 00:12.357
Hi, my name is Ryan Etheridge and you are listening to our podcast series focused around the gospel of Christ according to Matthew.

00:13.038 --> 00:21.913
Today's date is Thursday, March 5th and our scripture focus is going to be centered on Matthew chapter 24 verses 1 through 14.

00:21.933 --> 00:27.442
Now at this point in the gospel of Matthew

00:27.522 --> 00:40.498
Jesus is coming towards the end of his working ministry, meaning that he's being a little bit more blunt and honest and straightforward with his disciples, teaching in parables still, but now

00:40.610 --> 00:44.658
explaining the meaning behind most of his parables.

00:45.400 --> 00:55.640
So he started to give the disciples and his audience real challenges and started to teach them just previously in chapter 22.

00:56.141 --> 00:58.706
We read about the most important commandment.

00:58.850 --> 01:05.638
And at this point we're also seeing the disciples, you know, get a little uneasy about what's coming down the road for them.

01:05.658 --> 01:09.943
They're not certain, and so they're certainly having their first true test of faith here.

01:10.483 --> 01:23.058
And so that's where we pick up with today in chapter 24, where Jesus foretells the future for what's coming down the road, both for him and the disciples, and I guess the early Christian church, if you want to think of it that way.

01:23.586 --> 01:29.453
Now, today I do want to begin by reading our selected passage out loud in its entirety.

01:29.693 --> 01:32.297
But as I do so, here's what I want.

01:32.857 --> 01:41.748
I want you to hear what Christ is saying and ask yourself, how much of this has already happened or maybe happens in a natural historical cycle?

01:42.349 --> 01:45.693
How much of this is happening in our world right now?

01:46.654 --> 01:50.519
How many of these events can I see happening maybe in the future of my life?

01:50.599 --> 01:53.042
Maybe I can foresee or foreshadow that

01:53.122 --> 01:56.165
these events might come true later on in my life.

01:56.546 --> 02:00.310
So here's Matthew 24 verses 1 through 14.

02:02.192 --> 02:07.538
As Jesus was leaving the temple grounds, his disciples pointed out to him the various temple buildings.

02:08.019 --> 02:10.782
But he responded, do you see all these buildings?

02:11.343 --> 02:12.224
I tell you the truth.

02:12.664 --> 02:14.546
They will be completely demolished.

02:14.907 --> 02:17.950
Not one stone will be left on top of another.

02:18.831 --> 02:21.234
Later, Jesus sat on the Mount of Olives.

02:21.378 --> 02:26.426
His disciples came to him privately and said, tell us, when will all of this happen?

02:27.006 --> 02:31.133
What sign will signal your return and the end of the world?

02:31.994 --> 02:40.126
Jesus told them, don't let anyone mislead you, for many will come in my name, claiming I am the Messiah.

02:40.807 --> 02:47.037
They will deceive many, and you will hear of wars and threats of wars, but don't panic.

02:47.658 --> 02:50.642
Yes, these things must take place, but

02:50.722 --> 02:52.984
The end won't follow immediately.

02:53.645 --> 02:58.450
Nation will go to war against nation and kingdom against kingdom.

02:59.271 --> 03:02.835
There will be famines and earthquakes in many parts of the world.

03:03.396 --> 03:07.921
But all this is only the first of the birth pains with more to come.

03:07.961 --> 03:12.125
Then you will be arrested, persecuted and killed.

03:12.566 --> 03:16.530
You will be hated all over the world because you are my followers.

03:16.866 --> 03:20.912
And many will turn away from me and betray and hate each other.

03:21.573 --> 03:25.078
And many false prophets will appear and will deceive many people.

03:25.999 --> 03:31.527
Sin will be rampant everywhere and the love of many will grow cold.

03:32.228 --> 03:35.833
But the one who endures to the end will be saved.

03:36.353 --> 03:42.582
And the good news about the kingdom will be preached throughout the whole world so that all nations will hear it.

03:43.063 --> 03:45.266
Then the end day will come.

03:47.842 --> 03:50.726
Now, that is a lot to take in.

03:51.367 --> 03:56.854
I imagine that might have been one of the hardest things that Jesus told the disciples for them to process, right?

03:57.314 --> 03:58.736
But back to my earlier questions.

04:00.518 --> 04:02.821
And let's just go ahead and name it in the room.

04:03.402 --> 04:11.232
There's a lot of sudden conflict, particularly in the Middle East, that has popped up just this past week or so, right?

04:11.993 --> 04:16.018
And so when you look at this verse and you ask yourself, what's happening

04:16.098 --> 04:18.021
today in the world around us.

04:18.421 --> 04:25.230
It's easy to say, oh my goodness, every single one of those things is happening right now or has happened in the past.

04:25.871 --> 04:27.594
Are we near the end times, right?

04:28.074 --> 04:29.516
Surely we must be coming close.

04:30.538 --> 04:32.460
I mean, just you can name it, right?

04:32.821 --> 04:35.204
False prophets will appear and we'll deceive many people.

04:35.605 --> 04:37.387
We've seen our fair share of those, right?

04:37.888 --> 04:40.071
Sin will be rampant everywhere.

04:40.551 --> 04:42.514
My goodness, right?

04:42.594 --> 04:51.289
look at what these youth and these kids have to deal with just in the hallways at school or when they open their phone or their tablet, right?

04:51.930 --> 05:01.426
And it's all we can do to shield them from seeing something that we don't want them to see or we know that is negative or just downright sinful.

05:01.666 --> 05:02.086
What else?

05:02.287 --> 05:02.667
I don't know.

05:02.987 --> 05:03.788
Take your pick, right?

05:04.068 --> 05:06.671
Nation will go to Oregon's nation, kingdom against kingdom.

05:06.991 --> 05:11.115
There will be famines and earthquakes and natural disasters in many parts of the world, right?

05:11.595 --> 05:14.618
All of these things, prosecution of Christians, right?

05:14.678 --> 05:15.159
Martyrdom.

05:15.799 --> 05:17.121
All of this is listed here.

05:17.981 --> 05:21.264
So, I want you to take all that with a grain of salt now.

05:21.705 --> 05:26.569
Stay with me, and let's find a way through this tough passage together.

05:28.011 --> 05:31.474
The first thing that Jesus tells them in verse two,

05:31.842 --> 05:33.704
where he tells them about, do you see all these buildings?

05:33.784 --> 05:38.329
Not one of them will remain standing, not one stone left on top of another.

05:39.010 --> 05:42.794
I picture the disciples walking along, maybe thinking about it to themselves quietly.

05:43.134 --> 05:50.222
Maybe there were some who were even discussing it through whispers to each other, asking about what was the meaning about what Jesus had just said.

05:50.262 --> 05:52.304
Did you hear what he said?

05:52.945 --> 05:53.545
What does he mean?

05:53.605 --> 05:55.708
The temple buildings will all be destroyed.

05:56.148 --> 05:57.810
That doesn't sound like a good thing.

05:58.594 --> 06:07.443
Of course, we then see in verse three, once they all get to the Mount of Olives, that they were curious, and they had been thinking about what Jesus had started to say.

06:07.803 --> 06:09.946
So, they ask Jesus directly.

06:09.966 --> 06:17.033
A side note here that I really think we can draw some wisdom from the disciples in this moment.

06:17.714 --> 06:26.002
Think about how often do we maybe have a question, or a worry, or a doubt about life, faith, or spirituality, you name it.

06:26.114 --> 06:40.712
Instead of speaking about it to others, we just let it fester in our own minds instead of being direct and just asking for help or advice or seeking the wisdom of someone else who can interpret for us better than we can.

06:41.012 --> 06:42.053
How often do we do that?

06:42.354 --> 06:45.577
In other words, don't let any stone go unturned.

06:46.398 --> 06:48.000
If you have a question, ask it.

06:48.120 --> 06:50.183
If you have a worry, then pray about it.

06:50.303 --> 06:52.746
If you have a doubt, then talk about it.

06:54.408 --> 06:56.050
Now, for us today,

06:56.226 --> 07:09.906
I don't think it's necessarily useful or helpful to live a life that is in a constant state of worry or fear or concern that we are near the beginning of the end times.

07:10.567 --> 07:23.506
Now, of course, I'm fully aware to the immense and vast access that we all have to world news and information and current events on a global scale.

07:24.130 --> 07:43.338
if we are only living life, if we are only viewing the world through the lens in which we see the news stations feeding it to us or the media or whatever, then yes, we are probably going to be more pessimistic than optimistic in our outlook or opinion of the world and those around us.

07:44.500 --> 07:48.466
Now, I say all this as somebody who has

07:48.674 --> 07:56.564
Personally struggled and lived through some severe anxiety issues across different seasons of my life for different reasons.

07:56.904 --> 08:11.122
But along with that, I've also had the opportunity to be a co-pilot alongside family members and loved ones who are living and learning through their own struggles of worry and anxiety.

08:12.514 --> 08:34.460
There will inevitably be times in each of our lives, regardless of our age or how much life we expect to have ahead of us, where when we think about the future, when we try to consider a plan that will come for us down to the road, then we can easily spiral into a negative loop of what if scenarios, right?

08:34.700 --> 08:39.986
And those only draw us deeper into that state of worry, concern, and anxiousness.

08:40.098 --> 08:43.945
Of course, we know that's where the enemy would love to keep us, right?

08:44.185 --> 08:46.309
But that's not what God calls for our life.

08:47.371 --> 08:51.197
Maybe it's concern for our family.

08:51.919 --> 08:53.922
Maybe it's a spouse or our children, right?

08:54.563 --> 08:57.528
Will they make good choices for themselves and their family?

08:58.210 --> 09:00.534
What will happen to them if I'm not around?

09:01.756 --> 09:03.058
But like I said,

09:03.490 --> 09:12.284
I don't think Jesus gives us and his disciples this stark message in order to have us live life in constant worry or fear or anxiety.

09:12.625 --> 09:23.122
But instead, it's the opposite, to make sure that we are always ready, always on our guard, to make sure that we are living a life in accordance with Scripture.

09:23.330 --> 09:30.941
that we can be boldly confident that we are His children and He has good plans, no matter what happens, right?

09:31.321 --> 09:33.825
Plans to prosper us and not to harm us.

09:34.225 --> 09:37.530
Plans to give us a hope and a future, right?

09:37.690 --> 09:39.833
Jeremiah 29.11, we love that one.

09:41.275 --> 09:51.890
As we know from other words of Christ later on in this very chapter, Christ says, no one will know the time nor the hour when these things will happen.

09:52.258 --> 10:00.268
And then also a while back during the sermon on the mountain chapter six, when he teaches us, do not worry about tomorrow's troubles.

10:00.648 --> 10:02.690
For tomorrow will bring its own worries.

10:03.151 --> 10:06.235
Today's troubles are enough on their own.

10:06.675 --> 10:08.177
And I love that verse so much.

10:08.197 --> 10:09.038
Let me read it one more time.

10:09.518 --> 10:12.782
Jesus says this, do not worry about tomorrow's troubles.

10:13.303 --> 10:15.806
For tomorrow will bring its own worries.

10:16.206 --> 10:19.250
Today's trouble are enough on its own.

10:20.066 --> 10:25.853
Now, this doesn't mean we shouldn't plan and prepare for the future so that we can be ready when opportunities come, right?

10:26.173 --> 10:32.641
But for me, personally, this helps squash a lot of anxiety that pops up early in the morning, right?

10:32.981 --> 10:39.228
Or when I start to go down and think about all that I have to do this week, this month, that I want to accomplish this year, right?

10:39.569 --> 10:47.698
This helps me slow down, and especially as a musician, if I'm trying to learn more music or memorize more pieces, right?

10:47.778 --> 10:59.718
It's very easy for me to have a large platter of what I want to do, but to look at it all in one go is overwhelming and maybe I decide just to not practice anything new because I don't know where to start.

11:00.098 --> 11:04.586
But this verse is a beautiful and practical or spiritual purposes, right?

11:05.066 --> 11:07.250
Focus on today's progress.

11:07.522 --> 11:09.604
What can you make happen today?

11:09.965 --> 11:14.690
Where is God calling you to take that next step or to speak that next thing, right?

11:15.030 --> 11:19.055
Or to give that forgiveness or to give that grace or extend that mercy?

11:19.155 --> 11:20.817
Whatever it is, right?

11:21.558 --> 11:23.300
Do not worry about tomorrow's troubles.

11:23.560 --> 11:24.461
Focus on today.

11:24.841 --> 11:26.363
Do the work we have for it today.

11:26.743 --> 11:28.966
We'll get to tomorrow when tomorrow comes.

11:30.227 --> 11:36.274
Now, as a child or youth, I don't remember when, but when I first put these two points together,

11:36.418 --> 11:53.700
I developed this logic that worked really well for me at a young age to get myself out of one of those negative thought cycles and navigate anxiety or worry, specifically anxiety or worry about the future or the state of the world that we live in.

11:55.082 --> 12:04.114
If no one will know the day or the hour, if that is true, like Christ said, then anytime I or someone else

12:04.290 --> 12:08.995
thinks that the day or the hour is near, it must be false, right?

12:09.015 --> 12:10.876
Because no one's going to know, right?

12:11.297 --> 12:12.498
So that takes the load off.

12:12.718 --> 12:32.978
Now, as an adult, that still holds up and works for me a little bit, but I also understand the reality that it often seems that the bad, the negative, the hurtful, harmful, and hateful all seem to get more airtime than the good, the positive, the bold, the bright, and the beautiful.

12:34.114 --> 12:39.700
I think therein lies our mission as believers and followers of Christ.

12:40.481 --> 12:44.746
We are to be the light in a world that often looks dark.

12:45.547 --> 12:48.090
It sounds cliche, but it's so, so true.

12:48.130 --> 12:51.213
We are the light.

12:51.974 --> 12:54.437
Or at least we should be, right?

12:56.179 --> 13:02.706
What would the world around us look like if every single Christian asked themselves before they spoke

13:02.850 --> 13:05.193
typed, responded, or acted in some way?

13:05.993 --> 13:07.135
Is my next step?

13:07.575 --> 13:11.319
Are these words going to bring light into the world?

13:11.980 --> 13:15.243
Or is it going to bring and feed into more darkness?

13:16.184 --> 13:19.127
Now, that was just if every Christian asked that question.

13:19.167 --> 13:26.335
What if every single human, regardless of religious affiliation, chose to live and think in this way?

13:26.976 --> 13:27.757
That would be beautiful.

13:28.157 --> 13:32.722
The world would be an even more beautiful place than it already is, right?

13:33.026 --> 13:38.535
If there is darkness that we see, it is our purpose to bring light.

13:39.076 --> 13:50.834
But we can only bring light if we ourselves are ready, if we are in line with Christ and we have the one who shines in us close and in our hearts.

13:52.162 --> 13:56.368
I hope this podcast reading has been a blessing to you as it has been to me.

13:56.749 --> 14:03.799
And remember, be grateful today and every day for each of us have something to be thankful for.

14:03.859 --> 14:14.955
Thank you for listening to this podcast, focused around the book of Matthew, produced by the marvelous Kinney Stewart from the beautiful Perdido Bay Methodist Church.

14:15.395 --> 14:17.298
We hope you have a great day.

